<subSubSection id="C314653CFFC8FFA1FF0EFE92EAC11947" box="[199,1436,295,320]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB136B7FFC8FFA1FF0EFE92EAC11947" blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" box="[199,1436,295,320]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B97AEAA5FFC8FFA1FF0EFE92EE1C1938" bold="true" box="[199,321,295,320]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species has a black mesoscutum, two lsc, several fb, and a large surstylus with many spinules.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314653CFFC8FFA1FF0EFEFEEEE61C44" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB136B7FFC8FFA1FF0EFEFEEBEA1A47" blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B97AEAA5FFC8FFA1FF0EFEFEEE04191C" bold="true" box="[199,345,331,356]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Description.</emphasis>
MALE. Head including antenna and palpus yellow; frons shining, brown-tinged on dorsal 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FAB9FEF9EA22191C" box="[1392,1407,332,356]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FA43FEF9EACA191C" box="[1418,1431,332,356]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
; ocellar triangle black; first antennal flagellomere brownish surrounding base of arista, arista black. Thorax shining, brownish yellow; mesoscutum brownish black behind transverse suture, indistinctly divided by central brownish line, extending obliquely to dorsal corners of pale brown postpronotal lobes and entirely to lateral sides of scutum; notopleuron, anatergite, katatergite and mediotergite blackish brown; scutellum brownish black. Wing slightly infuscated around apical quarter of R 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FDFFFDBAED631A65" box="[566,574,527,541]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FD8EFDBAED131A65" box="[583,590,527,541]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
; calypter gray, with margin dark brown, fringe pale brown; halter brownish yellow. Legs yellow. Abdomen shining, brownish black; cercus whitish yellow. Bristles black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136B7FFC8FFA1FF0EFDFEEA281AD2" blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Frons 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FEC4FDFFEE6D1A1A" box="[269,304,586,610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as wide as eye, almost parallel-sided; second or 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FC5BFDFFECFD1A1A" box="[914,928,586,610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FC60FDFFECEB1A1A" box="[937,950,586,610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
as long as first or; oc 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FB62FDFFEBE81A1A" box="[1195,1205,586,610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FB76FDFFEB921A1A" box="[1215,1231,586,610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
as long as first or; poc almost as long as second or; gena 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FD8EFDDAED0C1AFF" box="[583,593,623,647]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FD95FDDAED361AFF" box="[604,619,623,647]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
as high as eye; pm four. First antennal flagellomere slightly shorter than wide, minutely pilose; arista plumose, with longest pubescence about 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FC6FFD27ECED1AD2" box="[934,944,658,682]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FC73FD27EC971AD2" box="[954,970,658,682]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
as long as width of first flagellomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136B7FFC8FFA1FF0EFD0DEBA51B45" blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Mesoscutum with two dc, six rows of acr but these very sparse behind level of first dc and four rows ending before scutoscutellar suture; scutellum with two lsc, of which anterior one 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FC2EFD6FECAC1A8A" box="[999,1009,730,754]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FC32FD6FEB561A8A" box="[1019,1035,730,754]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0">4</number>
as long as asc. Wing 
<quantity id="4CF69B52FFC8FFA1FACDFD6FEA061A8A" box="[1284,1371,730,754]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
long; costa with three sections in proportion of 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FDB9FD4AEDD11B6F" box="[624,652,767,791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="35.0">35</number>
: 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FD6DFD4AED9D1B6F" box="[676,704,767,791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="10.0">10</number>
: 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FD1EFD4AEDBA1B6F" box="[727,743,767,791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="6.0">6</number>
, r-m at distal 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FC4CFD4AECD21B6F" box="[901,911,767,791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FC52FD4AECF41B6F" box="[923,937,767,791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
of cell dm, M 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FB85FCBBEB091B64" box="[1100,1108,782,796]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
ratio 4.0, ultimate section of CuA 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FF05FC80EF891B3B" box="[204,212,821,835]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FF13FC90EFB91B45" box="[218,228,805,829]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FF27FC90EFA31B45" box="[238,254,805,829]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
as long as penultimate section. Fore femur with several fb; mid tibia with dp and one spur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136B7FFC8FFA1FF0EFCF9EDE01B8C" blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Epandrium with surstylus (
<figureCitation id="13352A32FFC8FFA1FDC9FCF9EDDA1B1C" box="[512,647,844,868]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[194,1382,198,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[186,1393,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Male genitalia of Sobarocephala megastylis sp. nov. (19 – 22, holotype) and Tetrameringia maculata sp. nov. (23, 24, paratype). See Figs 1 – 3 for explanation of parts. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205908/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs 19, 20</figureCitation>
) extremely large, bearing dense setae on outer and inner sides, and about 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FF12FCC5EFAA1BF0" box="[219,247,880,904]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="35.0">35</number>
spinules in two or three irregular rows along inner anteroventral margin; cercus small; proctiger V-shaped. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="13352A32FFC8FFA1FEFEFC21EED11BD4" box="[311,396,916,940]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[194,1382,198,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[186,1393,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Male genitalia of Sobarocephala megastylis sp. nov. (19 – 22, holotype) and Tetrameringia maculata sp. nov. (23, 24, paratype). See Figs 1 – 3 for explanation of parts. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205908/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FEA6FC21EED11BD4" box="[367,396,916,940]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
) with two long and three short setae; postgonite setulose apically. Phallapodeme 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FA8BFC21EA311BD4" box="[1346,1388,916,940]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="360.0">360</number>
µm long; phallus (
<figureCitation id="13352A32FFC8FFA1FEF4FC0DEECD1BA8" box="[317,400,952,976]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[194,1382,198,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[186,1393,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Male genitalia of Sobarocephala megastylis sp. nov. (19 – 22, holotype) and Tetrameringia maculata sp. nov. (23, 24, paratype). See Figs 1 – 3 for explanation of parts. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205908/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FEBAFC0DEECD1BA8" box="[371,400,952,976]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FE6BFC0DEE911BA8" box="[418,460,952,976]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="210.0">210</number>
µm long, mesophallus narrow, distiphallus spatulate, paraphallus minutely spinulose apically; ejaculatory apodeme short, 
<number id="3DC62490FFC8FFA1FDFDFC69ED0D1B8C" box="[564,592,988,1012]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="35.0">35</number>
µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136B7FFC8FFA1FF0EFBB5EEE81C60" blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" box="[199,437,1024,1048]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Body length 
<quantity id="4CF69B52FFC8FFA1FE9EFBB5EEEC1C60" box="[343,433,1024,1048]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136B7FFC8FFA1FF0EFB90EEE61C44" blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" box="[199,443,1060,1085]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">FEMALE. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314653CFFC8FFA1FF0EFBFDEE8F1C18" box="[199,466,1096,1121]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
